BBC Radio Derby broadcaster Colin Bloomfield died at a hospice in Shrewsbury yesterday morning after battle with skin cancer . 
  Niall Horan has described him as a 'super great guy and great commentator' Fellow broadcasters have paid tribute to the 'perfect colleague' and 'consummate professional' Bloomfield worked at BBC Radio Derby for 10 years as a presenter and commentator . 
  He died at the age of 33 after battling skin cancer which spread from a mole . 
 